From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0019/N] defNewGeneration.cpp: explicit MAX2<uintx> at line 215

Same root cause as patch 0016. `MAX2(unaligned_survivor_size,
SpaceAlignment)` deduces T from two mismatched types under CHERI:

  - unaligned_survivor_size : uintx     (`unsigned __intcap`)
  - SpaceAlignment          : size_t    (`unsigned long`)

Both are `unsigned long` on a non-CHERI build, so deduction works.
On CHERI the types differ and the template is ignored. Pass an
explicit template arg.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md §6 (patch 0019)

--- a/src/hotspot/share/gc/serial/defNewGeneration.cpp
+++ b/src/hotspot/share/gc/serial/defNewGeneration.cpp
@@ -212,7 +212,7 @@
   if (survivor_size != _from_counters->max_size()) {
     _from_counters->set_max_size(survivor_size);
   }
-    survivor_size = MAX2(unaligned_survivor_size, SpaceAlignment);
+    survivor_size = MAX2<uintx>(unaligned_survivor_size, SpaceAlignment);
 }

 size_t DefNewGeneration::compute_new_size() {
